summary: An Ordinance providing for the cost and expense of the laying off, opening, extending and establishing of a public street and highway to be known as Bothell Way, from the intersection of East Seventy-fourth Street and Tenth Avenue Northeast, northeasterly to the intersection of East Eighty-fifth Street and Nineteenth Avenue Northeast produced, as provided in Ordinance No. 39782 of the City of Seattle, by the issuance and sale of bonds of the district created to pay therefor.
